# Day 3 - LLM Basics with Ollama

## What is an LLM
An LLM is a Large Language Model trained on large amounts of text to generate human-like responses.

## What I used today
- Ollama on Windows
- Llama 3.1 8B model
- Local API with Python requests

## What I learned
- A model can run locally on my laptop
- Ollama exposes a local API
- Python can call that API and print responses

## Key point
Local LLMs help me practice GenAI without paying for cloud API usage.